folder: Shore Boulevard & West End Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: Shore Boulevard - West End Avenue
text:
Shore Boulevard, at West End Avenue, at the western end of Sheepshead Bay, showing W. P. A. operations on the widening of the thoroughfare by filling in part of the Bay and reconstructing the bulkhead. Views 2 and 3 show sewer construction on the same project, viewing west on the Boulevard from near Beaumont Street.

View 1: September 26, 1935
Views 2,3: April 27, 1936

folder: Shore Boulevard & West End Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: Shore Boulevard - West End Avenue
text:
Shore Boulevard, east from near West End Avenue on Sheepshead Bay, showing the old bulkhead and part of the Bay which will later be filled in when the thoroughfare will be widened. View 2 shows the new bulkhead line (left) and fill. These operations are by the W. P. A. and are part of the city's belt highway project.

View 1: March 16, 1936
View 2: June 24, 1936

folder: Shore Boulevard & West End Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: Shore Boulevard - West End Avenue
text:
Shore Boulevard, east from West End Avenue, along the shore of Sheepshead Bay. The views show operations being conducted by the W. P. A. in the widening of the thoroughfare. A new bulkhead line had to be constructed and part of the bay filled in to a depth of about twenty feet. On the north side of Sheepshead Bay (left) is Emmons Avenue, which is also being widened as part of the circumferential highway system which will girt the city.

View 1: July 21, 1936
View 2: August 25, 1936
View 3: September 11, 1936
View 4: September 24, 1936

Works Progress Administration
Five Boroughs Project

folder: Shore Boulevard & West End Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: Shore Boulevard - West End Avenue
text:
Shore Boulevard, north from West End Avenue to Emmons Avenue, showing a W. P. A. sewer and highway project at the western extremity of Sheepshead Bay, the buildings in the four views being on the north side of Emmons Avenue. The widening of Emmons Avenue is part of the city's circumferential highway system and necessitated the filling of part of Sheepshead Bay.

Views 1,2: July 21, 1936
View 3: August 25, 1936
View 4: September 24, 1936
